# Footer Schema Structure

The footer section of the application is populated via the Strapi backend API. The endpoint provides a structured schema that defines the layout and content of the site footer.

## API Endpoint

```
GET https://api.infinity.rgbgroup.ir/api/footer?populate[0]=First.Links&populate[1]=Second.Links&populate[2]=Third.Links&populate[3]=ContactUs
```

## Schema Structure

The footer schema consists of the following main sections:

### Column Sections (First, Second, Third)

Each column in the footer has:
- `Header`: The title of the column
- `Links`: An array of link objects containing:
  - `Title`: Display text for the link
  - `URL`: Target path for the link

### Contact Us Section

Contains contact information:
- `Phone`: Phone number for customer support
- `Whatsapp`: WhatsApp contact (nullable)
- `Instagram`: Instagram profile link (nullable)
- `Telegram`: Telegram contact (nullable)

### Customer Support

Text describing customer support hours and availability.

## Sample Implementation

When implementing the footer component, you should:
1. Fetch the footer data from the API
2. Parse the response into appropriate sections
3. Render each section according to the design
4. Handle proper loading states and error cases

## Related Components

- Footer component: Should consume this data structure
- Layout components: Should integrate the footer
- API service: Should include methods to fetch footer data

